); black. Labrum dark brown or infuscate (but often hidden under clypeus). Mesopleuron entirely black; upper half of mesepisternum with fine punctures of regular size and distribution. Lancet ( Figs 5, 6 ): 13 annuli; denticles occupying only about half width of basal or medial annulus.
